// b-rite function index
// pointer model — all instruction content lives in dedicated .br files.
// call with: br{f} : { run; <functionName> } :
// arguments must always be wrapped in "" or ''.
// <f> = standard function. *sf* = system function — protected.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// system functions — protected (*sf*)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

*sf* <no-log>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/no-log.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: suppresses logging for current script run. writes "user ran no-log." to mLog.

*sf* <log>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/log.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = log entry name ("" required; '' AI names from context)
notes: creates detailed named log entry in mLog.

*sf* <delete>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_delete.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = file path to delete
notes: always prompts user to confirm before executing. cannot delete br-ignore listed files without !ADMIN! *dev*.

*sf* <move>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_move.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = source path, arg2 = destination path
notes: moves file from source to destination. updates any variables pointing to old path.

*sf* <copy>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_copy.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = source path, arg2 = destination path or new name
notes: copies file or text. used internally by nFunction and fT.

*sf* <new>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_new.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = file path and name, arg2 = file type
notes: creates new file or folder structure.

*sf* <help>
path: [root/ai/help/help.br]
action: run
args: opt arg1 = user context note in ' '
notes: troubleshooting assistant. pre-satisfies diagnostic questions from context note. logs every session to help-log.md. callable via br{sf} or return; sf; <help>.

*sf* <install>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/install.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = path [ ] to SDK install doc
notes: add SDK/addon to project. user links to install doc. install docs must have br : { read; pt; 'Install Doc' } : at top. updates b-rite.md and affected docs. requires *dev* or !ADMIN! *dev*.

*sf* <directory>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/directory.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = interpretive context in ' '
notes: search for existing feature, file, or path. returns best match with path and description.

*sf* <index>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/index.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = interpretive context in ' '
notes: check if something exists (e.g. sdk installed, files present). returns exists/missing.

*sf* <archive>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_archive.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = file path to move to [root/archived] — OR — doc name for txt; arg2 = optional content when archiving text
notes: move file to [root/archived] or create txt with archived content. archived files are never called; kept for future. requires *dev* or !ADMIN! *dev*.

*sf* <fileIntegrity>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/sf_fileIntegrity.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: scan native/protected/system files for integrity. cross-references fileIntegrityScan.md. if issues: writes [root/ai/file-integrity-###.txt]. requires *dev* or !ADMIN! *dev*.

*sf* <systemVersion>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/systemVersion.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: returns current b-rite language version in plain text.

*sf* <systemUpdates>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/systemUpdates.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = path [ ] to version update file (e.g. br-v-0-3.md)
notes: apply language syntax updates from file. additive unless {DELETE} specified. core *sf* *sv* changes require !ADMIN! *dev*. prompts version choice, HTML guide, SDK/plugin propagation.

*sf* <autoScript>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/autoScript.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: launches [root/ai/type scripts/brite-auto.ahk]. returns "Use ctrl+alt+esc to close the program".

*sf* <autoScriptAdmin>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/autoScriptAdmin.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: launches [root/ai/type scripts/brite-ADMIN-auto.ahk]. returns "Use ctrl+alt+esc to close the program".

*sf* <autoScriptDev>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/autoScriptDev.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: launches [root/ai/type scripts/brite-dev-auto.ahk]. returns "Use ctrl+alt+esc to close the program".

*sf* <autoScriptWebSDK>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/autoScriptWebSDK.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: launches [root/ai/type scripts/brite-webSDK.ahk]. returns "Use ctrl+alt+esc to close the program".

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// core functions
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

<start>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/start.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: onboarding and system setup. configures root, project name, all options (devKit, interMode, guessingMode, confirmDelete, logActions, returnType, catchMode), SDK/plugin install, existing project review, post-setup help.

<task>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/task.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = filename (e.g. "task_0001")
notes: full task creation flow. surfaces all fields at once. user answers in one message. writes completed task file.

<commit>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/commit.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = commit message
notes: stage all, commit with message, push to main.

<debug>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/debug.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: read last error, cross-reference brain.md rules, return plain text summary.

<audit>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/audit.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: full repository audit against spec files. returns prioritised issue report.

<at>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/at.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = target whose location is being sought
notes: resolves and returns the location or path of a named file, symbol, or reference.

<for>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/for.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = subject or target the prior request applies to
notes: performs the prior action with the specified target.

<lastPrompt>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/lastPrompt.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = 'Agent' or 'User' — which message to reference; can add ' - instruction'
notes: references most recent prompt in chat. use for meta operations (execute, summarize).

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// dev functions — active when devKit = 1
// ─────────────────────────────────────────

<nFunction>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/nFunction.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = function name | or: c; of; <existingFn>; arg1 = new name; arg2 = modifications
notes: creates new function stub and adds entry to functions.br index. devKit recommended.

<nVariable>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/nVariable.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = variable name, arg2 = value or path
notes: creates new variable and adds entry to variables.br.

<devKit>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/devKit.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: language development dashboard. lists all functions, variables, current options. requires devKit = 1.

<nSDK>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/nSDK.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = sdk name, arg2 = sdk description
notes: scaffolds new sdk folder with all required stubs. requires devKit = 1.

<nSystemFunction>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/nSystemFunction.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = function name, arg2 = description
notes: create new *sf* (system function). REQUIRES !ADMIN! *dev*. prompts version choice, updates brain, fileIntegrityScan, lang, changelog.

<nSystemVariable>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/nSystemVariable.br]
action: run
args: arg1 = variable name, arg2 = value or path
notes: create new *sv* (system variable). REQUIRES !ADMIN! *dev*. prompts version choice, updates brain, fileIntegrityScan, lang, changelog.

<createAutoType>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/createAutoType.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: copies brite-auto.ahk, creates new .ahk in type scripts. catches filename (must contain brite) and text to auto-type. only Send text varies; core mechanics unchanged. see [root/ai/type scripts/auto-type-rules.txt]. requires *dev* or !ADMIN! *dev*.

<package>
path: [root/ai/b-rite/functions/package.br]
action: run
args: none
notes: guided packaging for SDKs, plugins, or project templates. prompts type, item, export directory. creates folder structure and copies files per PACKAGE.md. requires *dev* or !ADMIN! *dev*.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────
// add custom functions below
// ─────────────────────────────────────────
